## Autonomous Mode
When running in YOLO or autonomous mode:
- Install missing dev dependencies without asking (`pip install -q`, `npm install -D`)
- If Write tool is blocked by hooks, fall back to Bash heredoc (`cat > file`)
- If a command waits for interactive input, provide the safe default (y/enter/skip)
- Make reasonable decisions and log them to KNOWLEDGE.md
- Never block waiting for user input — decide, act, document

## Agent Usage Rules
- Use **qa-prompt-generator** for ALL QA, testing, or audit requests ("run QA", "test the site", "QA audit", "generate QA prompts")
- Use **test-writer** for writing unit/integration tests in code
- Use **repo-scorer** for evaluating repository health
- Use **security-auditor** for code-level security scanning
- Use **brand-aligner** for visual brand compliance
- Use **architecture-enforcer** for structural and pattern enforcement
- Use **code-reviewer** for pull request and code quality reviews
- Use **visual-verifier** for screenshot-based UI verification

## Command Shortcuts
- **"run QA"** or **"start QA"** → Use the qa-prompt-generator agent (`~/.claude/agents/qa-prompt-generator.md`). Read CLAUDE.md, extract project details, output pre-filled Comet prompts in 3 batches. Do NOT test the site yourself.
- **"onboard"** or **"onboard this project"** → Analyze codebase, generate CLAUDE.md, KNOWLEDGE.md, REVIEW.md, TASKS.md, run repo-scorer
- **"run preflight"** → Execute the PREFLIGHT checklist

## Git Workflow
Branch naming: type/short-description
Types: feat, fix, chore, docs, refactor, test, security

Convention:
- Never commit directly to main — always branch and merge
- main is always deployable (Coolify/CI deploys from main)
- Each Phase 3 wave = one branch (feat/wave-1-auth, feat/wave-2-crud, etc.)
- QA fix cycles = one branch per round (fix/qa-round-1, fix/qa-round-2)
- Delete branches after merging

Branch lifecycle:
  git checkout -b feat/short-description
  # ... work ...
  git add -A && git commit -m "feat: description"
  git push -u origin feat/short-description
  # merge to main (PR or direct merge for solo dev)
  git checkout main && git merge feat/short-description
  git push
  git branch -d feat/short-description
  git push origin --delete feat/short-description

